		{"id":"8565ba00249b4bc8","type":"text","text":"# Assigning IPV6\nTo assigning IPV6 make sure that your machine should have `static-hostname`\n\n```\n1. hostnamectl set-hostname nehraclasses.local\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ Setting static host-name\n\n2. hostnamectl\n```\n\n![[Pasted image 20250127014858.png]]\n\n#### let's assign IPV6\n\n```\n1. nmcli dev status\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ See the red network adapter we need to make connection for it then we can assign IP to it\n```\n\n![[Pasted image 20250127015053.png]]\n\n```\n2. nmcli connection add type ethernet con-name ens224 ifname ens224\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ Adding the connection for network adapter ens224. Also we can assgin IP as well in this command but for now leave it we will assign the IP using modify command\n\n3. nmcli connection show\n```\n\n![[Pasted image 20250127015417.png]]\n\n\n```\n4. nmcli connection modify ens224 ipv6.addresses \"fddb:fe2a:ad1e::c0a8:8/64\" ipv6.method manual\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ Modifying the connection by assigning IPV6 address to it \n\n5. cat /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ Show config details for connection ens224\n```\n\n![[Pasted image 20250127020014.png]]\n\n```\nAlso we can set the DNS and see the BOOTPROTO=dhcp we can modify it to manual and not assigned by DHCP and it is recommended to set the value BOOTPROTO=static for IPV6\n\n6. nmcli connection modify ens224 +ipv6.dns 2001:4860:4860::8888\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ Assigning DNS for IPV6\n\n7. vim ifcfg-ens224\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ open the ens224 connection file in vi-editor where we need to change BOOTPROTO=static\n\n8. nmcli connection reload\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ It will reload the entire network file\n\n9. nmcli connection up ens224\nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ Enabling the connection making status active\n\n10. ip a\n```\n\n![[Pasted image 20250127020846.png]]\n\n```\n11. ping fddb:fe2a:ad1e::c0a8:8\n    ping -6 fddb:fe2a:ad1e::c0a8:8\n    \nðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ Here -6 indicate you are using IPV6\n```","x":320,"y":-500,"width":920,"height":2900},
